Encapsulation:
private variable ---> To set: setter methods[can set one value at a time], To get: getter methods
private variable ---> To set: Constructors[Can set multiple values at a time], To get get: getter methods
private variable ---> To set: Constructors[Can set multiple values at a time], Update the values of private variables: Setter Methods, To get get: getter methods

private methods within public method --> Encapsulation

Constructors are primarily used for initializing object attributes when the object is created,
while setter methods are used to modify variables values after the object has been instantiated.

API: Constructor ---> SET
     Setter      ---> UPDATE

     ==============================================================================
     USAGES OF THIS KEYWORD:
     1. To differentiate between global variables and parameters name, if they are same
     2. BUILDER PATTERN